  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Resident Technical Officer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Lead and supervise the construction of luxurious bungalows by managing demolition, structural, and steel works while coordinating engineering activities to ensure timely progress and quality compliance.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead supervision of demolition activities to ensure safe and compliant execution on site</li><li>Oversee ERSS (Earth Retaining and Stabilizing Structures) works to maintain structural integrity and safety</li><li>Manage structural reinforced concrete (RC) works to meet design specifications and quality standards</li><li>Supervise structural steel work including fabrication and erection to ensure accuracy and safety compliance</li><li>Coordinate and oversee all necessary structural testing to validate construction quality and safety</li><li>Monitor construction progress and prepare detailed reports to inform stakeholders and support decision-making</li><li>Maintain and update comprehensive records of all engineering works and property documentation</li><li>Attend and actively contribute to site, progress, variation, and coordination meetings to align project objectives</li><li>Demonstrate leadership by supervising engineering building construction teams to achieve project milestones</li><li>Collaborate with multidisciplinary teams, including M&E coordination, to support integrated construction processes</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in Mechanical & Electrical (M&E) coordination to enhance project integration and efficiency</li></ul>",
